def: A salmon of small size; a samlet.
TO make foul; to soil; to defile. [Obs.] Milton.
Dark; gloomy; obscure; shaded; cheerless. [Poetic]He brought him through a darksome narrow pass To a broad gate, allbuilt of beaten gold. Spenser.
A unit of conductivity, being the reciprocal of the ohm.
The investing portion, or spherical envelope, surrounding theeccentric germinal spot of the germinal vesicle.
Any substance in the gaseous, or aëriform, state, the conditionof which is ordinarily that of a liquid or solid.
Fitted for, or carrying, a burden. Johnson.
A tendency of leaves or other organs of plants to have theirdorsal surface faced towards the rays of light.
A compound containing in the molecule two atoms of oxygenunited with some other element or radical; -- usually called dioxide,or less frequently, binoxide.
One of the auditory organs of certain medusæ; -- called alsoauditory tentacle.
